## folder stracture:
src/
├─ assets/ # fonts
├─ CLDR/ # hebrew jsons
├─ common/ # reusable UI building blocks: wizards, dialogs, inputs, ...
├─ css/ # global used css files
├─ i18n/ # js object of all the hebrew values by en keys
├─ interfaces/ # All the system objects interfaces and types
├─ pages/ # route entries used by react-router
├─ services/ # axios instances + endpoint defs
├─ stores/ # `zustand` stores of: UserState, WorkspaceState, MeltaPlusState, DraftsState, DarkModeState
├─ utils/ # shared custom hooks, functinos,complex basic components
├───── agGrid/ # All ag-grid basic components andc functions for manipulating data
├───── .../ # Move shared utils
└─ theme.ts # MUI theme
└─ App.tsx # This file defines the main React application component, handling user authentication, workspace setup, and global error/loading states, and serves as the entry point for rendering the app's core UI and analytics provider.


* Use `vite-tsconfig-paths` for path aliasing (`@/components/...`). :contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}  
* Set `build.target` to `"esnext"` unless you support legacy browsers—keeps bundles small.  
* Enable `react()` plugin’s `fastRefresh` in dev; let Vite handle production minification (esbuild/Terser). :contentReference[oaicite:9]{index=9}